The '''1989 Monte Carlo Open''' (also known as the '''Volvo Monte Carlo Open''' for sponsorship reasons) was a men's [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Clay court|outdoor clay courts]] at the [[Monte Carlo Country Club]] in [[Roquebrune-Cap-Martin]] in [[France]] that was part of the [[1989 Nabisco Grand Prix]]. The tournament was held from 24 April through 30 April 1989.

==Champions==
===Men's Singles===
{{main|1989 Monte Carlo Open – Singles}}
{{flagicon|ARG}} '''[[Alberto Mancini]]''' defeated {{flagicon|FRG}} [[Boris Becker]] 7–5, 2–6, 7–6, 7–5
* It was Mancini's 1st title of the year and the 3rd of his career.

===Men's Doubles===
{{main|1989 Monte Carlo Open – Doubles}}
{{flagicon|CSK}} '''[[Tomáš Šmíd]]''' / {{flagicon|AUS}} '''[[Mark Woodforde]]''' defeated {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Paolo Canè]] / {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Diego Nargiso]] 1–6, 6–4, 6–2
* It was Šmíd's 2nd title of the year and the 62nd of his career. It was Woodforde's 2nd title of the year and the 6th of his career.

