'''Bundesstraße 178''' (B178) is a [[Germany|German]] federal highway in the east of the [[Free State of Saxony|Saxony]]. It was built as a dual carriageway, and the highway connects with the motorway [[Bundesautobahn 4|A4]] near the city of [[Weißenberg]] in Saxony. It ends in [[Zittau]] to the [[Poland|Polish]] border. After crossing the Polish border, the road reaches the [[Czech Republic|Czech]] border after a few kilometres, where the Czech dual-carriageway [[R35 expressway|R35]] begins. In the future the road will be an international corridor in [[Central Europe]], connecting Germany with the west of Poland ([[Lower Silesian Voivodeship]]) and the Czech Republic.

The road is about {{convert|31|km}} long. The planned length, however, is {{convert|42|km}}.

