{{bilateral|Finnish–Polish|Finland|Poland}}
'''Finland–Poland relations''' refer to bilateral relations of [[Finland]] and [[Poland]]. Both countries are members of the [[European Union]] and the [[Council of the Baltic Sea States]].

Both countries established diplomatic relations on March 8, 1919. Finland has an embassy in [[Warsaw]] and an honorary consulate in [[Gdynia]]. Poland has an embassy in [[Helsinki]].

==Economic relations==
The value of two-way trade between Poland and Finland in 2015 totaled EUR 2.8&nbsp;billion.<ref name="spcc">{{cite web|title=ECONOMIC COOPERATION BETWEEN POLAND AND THE NORDIC COUNTRIES|url=https://www.spcc.pl/images/file/events_projects/2016/SPCC_Raport2015_EN_160615single.pdf|publisher=Scandinavian Polish Chamber of Commerce|page=33}}</ref>

==Agreements==
The two countries have two agreements regarding environmental protection signed in 1990.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ym.fi/en-US/International_cooperation/International_environmental_agreements|title=Environmental agreements – Ministry of the Environment|website=www.ym.fi}}</ref>

