{{Politics of Eritrea}}

The '''High Court of Eritrea''' is the [[final court of appeal]] in [[Eritrea]] and the highest court in the Eritrean judicial hierarchy. It has both original and [[appellate]] jurisdiction.

A panel of three [[judge]]s hears all original cases.  However, when the High Court is serving final appeals, a panel of five judges hears the trial.

In 2005, The High Court took an average of 2 months to decide if it would hear an appeal, and at year's end had a backlog of approximately 200 cases.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2006-08-01|url=https://www.state.gov/g/drl/rls/hrrpt/2005/61568.htm|title=Country Reports on Human Rights Practices (2005)}}</ref>

