{{Politics of Comoros}}

The '''Movement for Renewal and Democratic Action''' ({{lang-fr|Mouvement pour la Renovation et l'Action Democratique}}, MOURAD) was a political party in the [[Comoros]].

==History==
The party was established in 1990.<ref>Martin Ottenheimer & Harriet Ottenheimer (1994) ''Historical Dictionary of the Comoro Islands'', Scarecrow Press, p59</ref> It received 3.1% of the vote in the [[Comorian legislative election, 1992|1992 parliamentary elections]], winning one seat in the [[Assembly of the Union of the Comoros|Assembly of the Union]].<ref name=AI>[http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:CwSQeWwFLmsJ:www.africaintelligence.com/ION/politics/1992/12/05/no-legislative-majority,17598-ART%3FCXT%3DCANP%26country%3DCOMOROS%2520ISLANDS+&cd=4&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=uk Comoros Islands: No legislative majority] African Intelligence, 5 December 1992</ref>

