[[File:Placido_Rizzotto.jpg|thumb|right|Placido Rizzotto]]

'''Placido Rizzotto''' (Corleone, January 2, 1914 – March 10, 1948) was an [[Italians|Italian]] [[Italian Resistance|partisan]]<ref>http://lombardia.anpi.it/voghera/rizzotto/rizzotto.htm</ref>, [[socialist]] peasant and [[trade union]] leader from [[Corleone]], who was assassinated by [[Sicilian Mafia]] boss [[Luciano Leggio]]. Pieces of Rizzotto's mutilated body were discovered two years later at the bottom of a cliff with his limbs chained up, and a bullet hole in his head. When he was killed, Rizzotto was doing activist work with farm laborers, trying to help them take over unfarmed land on large estates in the area.<ref name = "whiteout-137">{{cite book  | last = Cockburn  | first = Alexander  | authorlink = Alexander Cockburn  |author2=[[Jeffrey St. Clair]]   | title = Whiteout, the CIA, drugs and the press  | pages= 137| publisher = [[Verso]]  | year=  1998  | location = [[NYC|New York]]  | isbn = 1-85984-258-5 }}</ref><ref name="midnight-104">{{cite book|title=Midnight in Sicily|author=Peter Robb|year=2007|publisher=Macmillan|isbn=978-0-312-42684-2|page=104|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FaQ7atNLeawC&pg=PA104}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=A passion for Sicilians: the world around Danilo Dolci|author=Jerry Mangione|publisher=Transaction|year=1985|isbn=978-0-88738-606-0|page=167|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0AlM3vxXp8gC&pg=PA167}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=The Mafia and politics, Volume 1966, Part 1|author=Michele Pantaleone|publisher=Chatto & Windus|year=1966|page=115|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uA8ZAAAAIAAJ&q=%22Placido+Rizzotto%22+%28Union+OR+unionist+OR+socialist%29&dq=%22Placido+Rizzotto%22+%28Union+OR+unionist+OR+socialist%29&hl=en&ei=tiZ4TMmAOIXGsAPNkuStBQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=10&ved=0CF4Q6AEwCQ}}</ref>

On May 24, 2012, nearly 65 years after his death, his remains were reburied in [[Sicily]] with state honors. The Italian government recognized in this way his achievement in standing up against the Italian Mafia.

