The '''Rally for Democracy and Progress''' ({{lang-fr|Rassemblement pour la démocratie et le progrès}}) is a [[political party]] in [[Chad]], led by [[Lol Mahamat Choua]].

The party was founded by Choua in December 1991 and was among the first batch of political parties to be legalized in March 1992.<ref>''Political Parties of the World'' (6th edition, 2005), ed. Bogdan Szajkowski, page 118.</ref> 

In the [[Chadian parliamentary election, 2002|parliamentary election]] held on 21 April 2002, the party, allied to the ruling [[Patriotic Salvation Movement]], won 12 out of 155 seats.

However, since the [[2005 Chad constitutional referendum]], which would allow President [[Idriss Déby]] to eliminate presidential terms, the RDP has been part of the opposition.

